                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3905: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-27T20:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 27, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 27—3:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Note received today from Amoedo, Burgos representative in Lisbon, designates
                    by degrees and minutes neutral zones in ports of Tarragona, Valencia, Alicante,
                    Cartagena and Barcelona. Full details can be sent by telegraph if desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
